The Mechanics: The Crumbling Floor
The ascent takes 4 rounds. Each round presents a new hazard.
Round 1: The First Volley
Hazard: A shower of smaller debris rains down.
Mechanic: Every character must make a Standard Agility check.
Failure: Take 4 Bludgeoning Damage from the falling stones.
Round 2: The Structural Failure
Hazard: A massive chunk of the shaft wall breaks free and slams into the side of the lift platform.
Read Aloud: "A boulder the size of a horse smashes into the edge of the platform. The stone floor fractures, cracks racing across the surface. A huge section of the lift crumbles away into the darkness below!"
Mechanic: The GM designates one-quarter of the platform as unstable. Any character standing in that zone must make a Hard (-2) Agility check to leap to a stable section.
Failure: The character falls with the debris, but manages to grab the edge of the platform. They are now hanging precariously over the shaft and must use their next turn to climb back up.
Round 3: The Archer's Last Stand
Hazard: As the lift ascends past the catwalks, the surviving Draugr Archers get one last look at you. They fire a final, desperate volley down into the shaft.
Mechanic: Every character must make a Hard (-2) Agility check to use the remaining platform for cover.
Failure: Take 2 Irreducible Damage from a well-aimed steel arrow.
Round 4: The Final Ascent
Read Aloud: "The light of the surface appears above, a promise of safety. With a final groan, the lift shudders to a halt, locking into place at the top of the shaft. You have made it."

